works.description: Seattle-based developer Greenfab has announced that the company will be assembling the city’s first modular home that targets the prestigious LEED Platinum certification. The home will consist of six boxes, each of which is 12 feet wide, 20 feet long and 16 feet high. Built at a factory in Idaho, the boxes will be part of a house that will have 1790sqf of area, with three bedrooms and 2.75 bathrooms.
